# AArch64 Advanced SIMD / NEON instruction encodings
# Source of truth for HELM's SIMD decoder — covers the subset used
# by real-world binaries (fish-shell, musl, etc.).
#
# Format: QEMU decodetree syntax.
#   Fixed bits: 0 / 1  |  Don't care: .  |  Field: name:width
#   Constraints: name=value  |  Comments: # ...
#
# This file is parsed by helm-decode at build time (build.rs) and
# generates both a name-decoder and a handler-trait dispatcher.

### Advanced SIMD copy / insert / extract

DUP_general     0 q:1 00 1110 000 imm5:5 0 0001 1 rn:5 rd:5
INS_general     0 1   00 1110 000 imm5:5 0 0011 1 rn:5 rd:5
UMOV            0 q:1 00 1110 000 imm5:5 0 0111 1 rn:5 rd:5
INS_element     0 1   10 1110 000 di:5   0 si:4  1 rn:5 rd:5

