### Advanced SIMD shift by immediate
# The shift-by-imm / fixed-point-convert patterns share the `11110 immh`
# encoding space with MOVI (modified immediate).  When immh == 0 the
# shift encodings are UNALLOCATED and MOVI matches instead.
# Within this {} overlap group, MOVI appears first so its fixed
# bits[23:19]=00000 catch the immh==0 case; shift patterns (with immh
# as a free field) match everything else.

{
### Advanced SIMD modified immediate (immh == 0 fallback)
MOVI            0 q:1 op:1 0 1111 00000 abc:3 cmode:4 01 defgh:5 rd:5

### Advanced SIMD shift by immediate
SHL_v           0 q:1 0 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 01010 1 rn:5 rd:5
SSHR_v          0 q:1 0 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 00000 1 rn:5 rd:5
USHR_v          0 q:1 1 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 00000 1 rn:5 rd:5
SSRA_v          0 q:1 0 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 00010 1 rn:5 rd:5
USRA_v          0 q:1 1 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 00010 1 rn:5 rd:5
SSHLL_v         0 q:1 0 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 10100 1 rn:5 rd:5
USHLL_v         0 q:1 1 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 10100 1 rn:5 rd:5
SHRN_v          0 q:1 0 0 11110 immh:4 immb:3 10000 1 rn:5 rd:5

